Description:
Annotation on the envelope: "Rubens (Falsett) Frhr A von Tucher"

- Correspondence with Hans-Joachim Falsett (dated 1956), with the administration of the Frh. V. Tuchersche Castle (dated 1967) and with the director of the Art History Department of the University of Marburg (dated 1956)
- Historical map of the area among Donauwörth, Eichstätt and Neuburg
- Program of the concerts in Leitheimer Castle in 1967
- Bibliographic references
- Photocopies and reproductions of the Portrait of 'Sophie-Henriette, marquise of Montperny (born countess of Castellane)' in Leitheim Castle
- Report by Hans-Joachim Falsett about the Portrait of Sophie-Henriette
